On this occasion, we remember one of his famous quotes: 'Success in any task requires not only dedication and strength but also strong will and initiative.' We hope that Tagore's words will guide us towards a new achievement.

Take out my heart before I'm laid to rest, Let not the one within be mixed with earth's behest, For in it beats a love so pure and true, That even death cannot its power subdue.  Let not the soil, with its decay and rot, Taint the love that within my heart is wrought, But let it soar above the earthly plane, A love eternal that forever will remain.  Take out my heart, but do not mourn or weep, For in death, my love shall only grow deep, And though my body may return to dust, My love will live on, unspoiled and just.
